The paper deals with an encoding scheme that is robust against noise and signal loss, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT). The scheme is also efficient in terms of transmitted power requirements, which could fall under distributed systems (cs.DS) or data compression (cs.DC). The paper also presents a model that describes the decoding process, which could be relevant to networked systems (cs.NI) or signal processing (cs.SI).
